  "description": "Review of attention as a neurocognitive system Review of attention as a neurocognitive system We\u0026#39;re habituated to think of attention as a little bit of property: something you either don\u0026#39;t have, or if you have it, you\u0026#39;re at risk of losing it.\nYet the more closely neuroscientists examine the phenomenon we call \u0026#34;paying attention,\u0026#34; the less it behaves like a static resource and more it resembles a dynamic system of relations, only ever existing because the environment it\u0026#39;s in makes it exist.\n",
